WEBVTT

00:10.488 --> 00:11.620
- And if God

00:13.752 --> 00:16.407
won't turn a blind eye to sin,

00:18.061 --> 00:19.062
why are we?

00:20.498 --> 00:21.456
Mm-mm.

00:23.327 --> 00:27.027
It's time, church.
[parishioners exclaiming]

00:27.070 --> 00:30.900
It's time that we
examine our hearts.

00:30.943 --> 00:33.337
'Cause I know that in that day,

00:33.381 --> 00:36.732
when the Lord decides
to call me home,

00:39.474 --> 00:44.479
I'll be standing at those
gates, Holy in his sight.

00:44.522 --> 00:48.091
And he'll look at
me and say Solomon,

00:48.135 --> 00:49.875
you called it what it was.

00:49.919 --> 00:54.010
Sin.
[parishioners exclaiming]

00:54.054 --> 00:57.622
Come on in, my good
and faithful servant.

01:00.103 --> 01:02.497
Now I don't know about you,

01:02.540 --> 01:06.588
I don't know about you,
I don't know about you,

01:06.631 --> 01:10.592
but I'll be runnin' into
the arms of my Lord.

01:10.635 --> 01:12.115
Oh.

01:12.159 --> 01:18.339
Free and clean.
[parishioners exclaiming]

01:18.382 --> 01:23.344
My sweet daughter Grace
is gonna come up and sing.

01:23.387 --> 01:29.132
As the spirit leads.
[parishioners exclaiming]

01:29.176 --> 01:32.309
[soft, tense music]

01:33.528 --> 01:35.007
Girl.

01:35.051 --> 01:37.401
I announced you to
the congregation.

01:37.445 --> 01:40.491
You should've already been
up there and ready to sing.

01:40.535 --> 01:41.971
- I know, daddy.

01:43.451 --> 01:46.715
I'm not feeling so good.

01:46.758 --> 01:51.981
Do I need to
rehearse this time?

01:56.594 --> 02:10.086
[tense piano music]

02:14.743 --> 02:20.705
♪ Amazing grace

02:20.749 --> 02:26.450
♪ How sweet the sound

02:26.494 --> 02:36.417
♪ That saved a wretch like me

02:36.460 --> 02:41.117
♪ I once was lost

02:41.161 --> 02:43.163
[door slams]

02:43.206 --> 02:49.343
[tense music]

02:59.440 --> 03:01.224
- Powerful message
today, Pastor.

03:01.268 --> 03:04.009
- God inspired,
brother, God inspired.

03:04.053 --> 03:05.968
- It sure was, it sure was.
[laughing]

03:06.011 --> 03:06.795
- Amen.

03:06.838 --> 03:08.275
- So Pastor?

03:08.318 --> 03:09.711
Why does God give
us these struggles

03:09.754 --> 03:11.234
if he knows we
can't resist them?

03:11.278 --> 03:13.758
- Oh.
- Why not just take 'em away?

03:14.933 --> 03:19.634
- Deacon Henry,
it is inevitable

03:19.677 --> 03:21.505
that stumbling
blocks will come.

03:21.549 --> 03:25.379
But woe unto the man
to whom they come.

03:25.422 --> 03:28.251
It would be better for
him if mill stone were

03:28.295 --> 03:31.211
hung around his neck and
he be thrown into the sea.

03:31.254 --> 03:32.603
[laughing]

03:32.647 --> 03:34.866
- What about his
mercy and grace?

03:34.910 --> 03:36.781
Your church need to
know they're forgiven.

03:36.825 --> 03:39.915
That's what the
word of God teaches.

03:41.264 --> 03:44.311
- Who is the, um,

03:44.354 --> 03:48.837
called and God ordained
pastor here, Deacon Jones?

03:48.880 --> 03:49.925
- You are, but I'm
just sayin' the way--

03:49.968 --> 03:52.144
- Drink up, boys.

03:52.188 --> 03:53.842
Let's drink up.

03:53.885 --> 03:55.887
[chuckling]

03:55.931 --> 03:57.106
Clea.

03:58.760 --> 04:00.414
Where is that girl?

04:02.111 --> 04:03.243
Go get her.

04:06.289 --> 04:08.509
[tense music]

04:08.552 --> 04:10.902
Just gotta know who's
in charge, boys.

04:10.946 --> 04:11.903
[men chuckle]

04:11.947 --> 04:13.775
You just gotta know.

04:13.818 --> 04:18.301
- [Deacon Jones] They do
indeed. They do indeed.

04:18.345 --> 04:20.912
[tense music]

04:21.957 --> 04:24.786
[barfing]

04:24.829 --> 04:26.309
[knocking]

04:26.353 --> 04:30.226
- Gracie?
[soft music]

04:30.270 --> 04:32.620
You all right?

04:32.663 --> 04:36.537
You've been in there
for a long time.

04:36.580 --> 04:39.104
[soft music]

04:41.585 --> 04:43.892
- Mom?
- Oh my God.

04:44.719 --> 04:47.635
[tense music]

04:47.678 --> 04:51.073
Oh my...
[tense music]

04:53.945 --> 04:56.687
- It's not my fault.
- What?

04:56.731 --> 04:58.080
What happened?

04:59.516 --> 05:02.127
Oh my god.

05:05.479 --> 05:07.481
- I'm honored to
introduced one of our

05:07.524 --> 05:11.746
highly esteemed colleagues in
the field of music therapy.

05:11.789 --> 05:14.357
In the five and half
years she's been
with this department,

05:14.401 --> 05:17.012
she has facilitated
an enriching

05:17.055 --> 05:19.493
environment for our scholars.

05:19.536 --> 05:23.061
In turn, they have gone out
and impacted their community

05:23.105 --> 05:26.282
with the knowledge
she's imparted.

05:26.326 --> 05:30.112
Today, that vision
is expanding.

05:30.155 --> 05:34.551
Please welcome to the stage,
Professor Grace Wyatt.

05:34.595 --> 05:39.251
[applause]
[cheering]

05:43.604 --> 05:45.910
- Thank you.

05:45.954 --> 05:49.697
I'd like to first thank
you all for being here.

05:49.740 --> 05:55.180
Without you, we really
couldn't do what we're doing.

05:55.224 --> 06:01.491
Music therapy embraces the
creative and the concrete,

06:01.535 --> 06:06.627
and not only are our
students versed in theory,

06:06.670 --> 06:10.979
instrument, and voice,
but also act of listening

06:11.022 --> 06:16.550
and sensitivity and
oh, monotonous hours
of clinical work.

06:16.593 --> 06:19.640
[laughing]

06:19.683 --> 06:22.382
You are amazing, and I am
so proud of you, Olivia.

06:22.425 --> 06:23.426
- Thank you.

06:23.470 --> 06:24.993
Thank you, professor.

06:25.036 --> 06:27.561
- I adore you, Doctor Wyatt.

06:27.604 --> 06:30.912
- And Mr. Wyatt, are the
wind beneath my wings.

06:30.955 --> 06:32.130
- Oh.

06:32.174 --> 06:34.045
- Hey, Eric, good to see you.

06:34.089 --> 06:35.699
Glad you could make it.

06:35.743 --> 06:37.048
- Well I wouldn't miss
the opportunity to see

06:37.092 --> 06:38.572
my beautiful queen shine.
- Ah.

06:38.615 --> 06:40.443
- Shine she does.
[laughing]

06:40.487 --> 06:44.273
I'm not supposed to say
anything, but uh, we got it.

06:44.316 --> 06:45.448
- What?

06:45.492 --> 06:46.928
Are you?

06:46.971 --> 06:48.625
How do you know?

06:48.669 --> 06:49.887
- Well, they're still
counting numbers but I can

06:49.931 --> 06:51.715
see it all over their faces.

06:51.759 --> 06:53.630
You did it, Grace.
- Oh, this is so wonderful.

06:53.674 --> 06:55.545
I'm going to have to
prepare my proposal,

06:55.589 --> 06:57.373
get it ready before I
show it to the board-

06:57.417 --> 06:58.983
- Yeah, I know, I know,
there'll be time for that.

06:59.027 --> 07:00.985
For right now, you
gotta savor this moment.

07:01.029 --> 07:02.944
And I wanna introduce you
to some more of the donors.

07:02.987 --> 07:04.075
- Okay.
- Come on.

07:04.119 --> 07:05.642
- Oh go ahead.

07:05.686 --> 07:06.469
I'm gonna go back to the
office for a little bit.

07:06.513 --> 07:07.252
- You sure?

07:07.296 --> 07:08.819
- Yeah.

07:08.863 --> 07:10.473
- But you'll be home
in time for dinner?

07:10.517 --> 07:11.822
- Oh, with the most
beautiful woman on Earth.

07:11.866 --> 07:13.215
Girl, you know I
wouldn't miss it.

07:13.258 --> 07:15.260
- You're so full of it.
- Oh.

07:15.304 --> 07:18.438
- I love you.
- Love you, babe.

07:18.481 --> 07:22.050
[soft music]

07:26.620 --> 07:32.016
♪ Could he possibly know

07:32.060 --> 07:36.847
♪ Possibly know

07:36.891 --> 07:45.247
♪ That my heart
belongs to him ♪

07:49.947 --> 07:57.564
[door bell rings]

08:02.264 --> 08:04.658
- [Officer] Hello ma'am,
are you Miss Wyatt?

08:04.701 --> 08:05.789
- Yes, I am.

08:09.010 --> 08:11.795
- Ma'am, I have some
really bad news.

08:11.839 --> 08:14.885
Your husband was killed as
a result of a car crash,

08:14.929 --> 08:16.844
and I am so sorry.

08:16.887 --> 08:21.413
I'm so sorry.
[tense, dramatic music]

08:25.766 --> 08:29.117
[glass shatters]

08:29.160 --> 08:31.336
[tense, dramatic music]

08:31.380 --> 08:32.903
- Why God?

08:35.515 --> 08:37.255
- Who is he?
- Solomon, please.

08:37.299 --> 08:39.388
Don't do this. Not here.

08:41.346 --> 08:46.090
- Train up your child,
and the way he should go,

08:46.134 --> 08:50.138
and when he is old, he
will not depart from it.

08:51.618 --> 08:55.230
Do you not have any
fear of the Lord?

08:55.273 --> 08:57.406
Any fear of your father?
- Please.

08:57.449 --> 09:01.715
- This the last time I'm
gonna ask you, who is he?

09:03.760 --> 09:05.675
- He raped me.

09:05.719 --> 09:07.634
I tried to tell you--
- No!

09:09.636 --> 09:12.856
- You lyin' jezebel!

09:12.900 --> 09:16.599
Deacon Henry is one of
the finest men I know.

09:16.643 --> 09:19.733
A true man of God!

09:19.776 --> 09:24.607
Deacon Henry is the biggest
supporter of my ministry.

09:24.651 --> 09:27.262
His checks keep the
church doors open.

09:27.305 --> 09:29.960
Why would you lie on a
man of God like that?

09:30.004 --> 09:32.789
Who you coverin' up for?

09:32.833 --> 09:37.577
- Solomon, why would you
talk to her like this?

09:37.620 --> 09:39.579
Our daughter is hurting.

09:39.622 --> 09:43.191
- Well maybe if you would've
been a better mother,

09:43.234 --> 09:45.889
your daughter wouldn't
be in this situation.

09:45.933 --> 09:47.064
I?

09:48.762 --> 09:51.895
I have decided to
walk in the light.

09:53.331 --> 09:57.248
[tense, dramatic music]

09:57.292 --> 10:00.077
And light have no
fellowship with darkness.

10:00.121 --> 10:02.253
- Daddy, I'm sorry.

10:04.734 --> 10:05.909
It wasn't my fault.

10:05.953 --> 10:08.259
- Stop the cryin'.

10:08.303 --> 10:11.915
You got yourself
into this mess.

10:11.959 --> 10:20.576
And I will be if I allow
it to take away my ministry.

10:20.620 --> 10:25.015
Preacher's daughter
all knocked up.

10:25.059 --> 10:27.670
How congregation will
look me in the eyes again?

10:27.714 --> 10:30.064
- I'm sorry, daddy.

10:30.107 --> 10:33.241
I didn't mean for it to happen.

10:33.284 --> 10:34.416
- Yeah.

10:36.940 --> 10:39.116
You girls never do.

10:39.160 --> 10:41.684
- Please, please believe me.

10:41.728 --> 10:43.468
- Mm-mm.

10:43.512 --> 10:47.864
Uh uh, my congregation is
not gonna see my daughter

10:47.908 --> 10:50.258
wearing her sin on her body

10:51.302 --> 10:53.740
like a-
[Clea yells]

10:53.783 --> 10:56.264
FLASHING RED LIGHT!

10:56.307 --> 11:00.137
Do you even care what
this is gonna cost me?

11:04.402 --> 11:07.536
- What are you saying, Solomon?

11:07.579 --> 11:10.974
[tense, dramatic music]

11:15.239 --> 11:21.028
- We gonna send her away,
to live with my sister.

11:21.071 --> 11:25.728
She can have that uh, uh,
that baby of hers over there.

11:27.295 --> 11:31.081
And nobody is to
know about her.

11:34.258 --> 11:36.652
I mean nobody.

11:36.696 --> 11:40.134
[tense, dramatic music]

11:42.702 --> 11:45.705
[door slams]

11:45.748 --> 11:51.711
[tense music]

11:56.454 --> 11:57.499
- I uh...

11:59.457 --> 12:01.329
I, I just wanna help.

12:03.548 --> 12:08.771
- Can you bring my
Eric back to me?

12:08.815 --> 12:10.773
Huh?

12:10.817 --> 12:14.690
Can you erase this nightmare?

12:19.390 --> 12:20.348
Wine?

12:22.393 --> 12:26.354
- Look, Grace, I don't know
all that you're going through

12:26.397 --> 12:30.880
or all that you're feeling-
- Oh no, no, you don't.

12:30.924 --> 12:32.577
- I want you to know
that you've been in

12:32.621 --> 12:35.102
my prayers every night since.

12:36.103 --> 12:37.800
- Prayers?

12:37.844 --> 12:40.063
[laughs]

12:42.283 --> 12:44.502
I never knew you to pray.

12:46.374 --> 12:48.550
- Yeah, I pray.

12:53.207 --> 12:56.253
- Well I don't
need your prayers.

12:56.297 --> 12:57.559
- Grace.

12:59.300 --> 13:01.258
You need help.

13:02.390 --> 13:05.436
Let God help you through this.

13:05.480 --> 13:07.003
- God?

13:11.660 --> 13:15.925
Don't, don't talk
to me about God.

13:15.969 --> 13:22.845
God took everything away from
me that mattered. Everything!

13:22.889 --> 13:26.414
My life was destroyed
in the church,

13:26.457 --> 13:32.420
and after everything
that happened to me,

13:32.463 --> 13:36.032
he took the only
thing that I had left.

13:36.076 --> 13:42.430
- Grace, Eric wouldn't want
you to be like this now.

13:42.473 --> 13:45.128
It's been six months.

13:45.172 --> 13:49.437
You've gotta pull
yourself together.

13:49.480 --> 13:52.092
Look, look, the
university wants you back.

13:52.135 --> 13:54.398
I can't keep stalling
them for you.

13:54.442 --> 13:56.574
That's been your life's work.

13:56.618 --> 13:59.012
You could pick up right
where you left off.

13:59.055 --> 14:02.754
It'll be good for you!

14:02.798 --> 14:06.541
Grace, stop it!

14:06.584 --> 14:10.806
You're not the only person
that's lost someone.

14:10.850 --> 14:13.156
I've lost, too.

14:14.244 --> 14:15.855
- I'm done.

14:17.334 --> 14:20.772
I'm done.
[tense music]

14:25.473 --> 14:29.433
- Well, please consider.

14:29.477 --> 14:33.873
I uh, I know a lady there.

14:33.916 --> 14:36.266
She's a good person.

14:36.310 --> 14:38.878
I know she'd love to meet you.

14:40.140 --> 14:46.276
[tense music]

15:08.603 --> 15:10.866
- [Clea] Gracie, is that you?

15:10.910 --> 15:12.694
- [Grace] Yes, mama, it's me.

15:12.737 --> 15:17.220
- Gracie. Have you been
gettin' all of my messages?

15:17.264 --> 15:19.657
We used to talk
every Sunday night

15:19.701 --> 15:22.356
and you know I look
forward to that.

15:22.399 --> 15:23.574
- [Grace] I know mama.

15:23.618 --> 15:26.229
- Are you mad at me again?

15:26.273 --> 15:29.232
Because I didn't
protect you the way that

15:29.276 --> 15:31.104
I should have when
you were young?

15:31.147 --> 15:34.716
- Mama, I told you
that that is the past,

15:34.759 --> 15:36.326
and there's no reason to-

15:36.370 --> 15:39.112
- 'Cause I don't know
what else I can do.

15:39.155 --> 15:41.636
And if I could
change things, I-

15:41.679 --> 15:43.029
- Mama.

15:44.073 --> 15:46.075
Just stop. Please stop.

15:48.512 --> 15:49.513
[kettle whistling]

15:49.557 --> 15:52.603
- [Clea] Your father.

15:52.647 --> 15:54.170
- [Grace] What about him?

15:54.214 --> 15:57.304
- Oh, he's been
askin' about you.

15:57.347 --> 15:58.696
- [Grace] No.

15:58.740 --> 16:00.916
- He asks about
you all the time.

16:00.960 --> 16:03.963
- [Grace] I said no.
I don't think so.

16:04.006 --> 16:07.314
- He's really not
doin' all that well.

16:07.357 --> 16:08.619
It would mean a lot.

16:08.663 --> 16:11.796
- I said no.

16:12.928 --> 16:14.625
- How is Eric?

16:14.669 --> 16:17.802
- Eric, Eric is gone.

16:20.370 --> 16:21.981
- Gone?

16:22.982 --> 16:24.287
Gone where?

16:24.331 --> 16:27.029
When is he comin' back?

16:27.073 --> 16:32.687
- Look, I should go.
It's getting late.

16:32.730 --> 16:35.211
I'll call you back soon.

16:35.255 --> 16:36.908
- [Clea] Okay, honey.

16:36.952 --> 16:42.044
You take care now.
[melancholy music]

16:54.796 --> 16:57.407
[door dings]

16:58.234 --> 17:02.369
[soft music]

17:10.812 --> 17:12.596
- Excuse me.

17:12.640 --> 17:15.077
Grace Grant.

17:15.121 --> 17:17.427
Uh, no, no, that's my um...

17:17.471 --> 17:20.082
- I know who you
are, and I'm sorry,

17:20.126 --> 17:21.910
but I told you the other
day that you have to have

17:21.953 --> 17:23.564
your doctor call in
a new prescription.

17:23.607 --> 17:25.087
- He did.

17:25.131 --> 17:28.221
Look, look, you haven't
even checked yet.

17:29.265 --> 17:32.703
[pharmacist sighs]

17:32.747 --> 17:36.664
[soft music]
[typing]

17:36.707 --> 17:39.014
- [Pharmacist]
There's nothing here.

17:39.058 --> 17:40.581
- But, He gets busy.

17:40.624 --> 17:44.237
Uh, look, all I need
is enough to hold me

17:44.280 --> 17:46.413
until we clear this up.

17:46.456 --> 17:49.416
- No, that's
against our policy.

17:49.459 --> 17:51.722
- You know me.

17:51.766 --> 17:55.204
I'm a professor at a
university and you are

17:55.248 --> 17:59.382
treating me like I'm
some bum off the street.

17:59.426 --> 18:01.210
- I am not doing that at all.

18:01.254 --> 18:03.734
I actually refilled two
prescriptions early for you,

18:03.778 --> 18:06.389
but this is, just nothing
else I can do about this

18:06.433 --> 18:07.956
until your doctor
says something.

18:07.999 --> 18:09.566
I'm sorry.

18:09.610 --> 18:12.482
There's nothing I can do.
- You are withhold-

18:12.526 --> 18:17.574
You are withholding necessary
medication from someone.

18:17.618 --> 18:18.532
Now...

18:20.142 --> 18:22.579
- I'm sorry.

18:34.504 --> 18:38.073
[heavy breathing]

18:42.643 --> 18:48.562
[tense music]
[heavy breathing]

18:53.262 --> 18:57.745
- God, I need your help.

18:57.788 --> 18:59.790
I need your help.

18:59.834 --> 19:02.097
[sobbing]

19:02.141 --> 19:05.361
[man humming]

19:10.061 --> 19:15.806
♪ Amazing grace

19:15.850 --> 19:17.765
♪ How sweet

19:17.808 --> 19:19.419
- Mm, mm mm mm.

19:19.462 --> 19:20.289
[chuckles]

19:20.333 --> 19:23.205
♪ The sound

19:23.249 --> 19:24.815
I told your father
that I'd take you home

19:24.859 --> 19:26.948
when we was finished
since I'd be heading

19:26.991 --> 19:28.950
in that direction anyway.

19:28.993 --> 19:30.734
- Thanks, Deacon Henry.

19:30.778 --> 19:33.476
- My absolute pleasure.

19:33.520 --> 19:38.742
You need some help with that?
[tense music]

19:38.786 --> 19:42.006
Do you even know what a
beautiful girl you are?

19:42.050 --> 19:45.053
I think about you
all the time, Grace.

19:45.096 --> 19:48.665
I can't believe how
you make me feel.

19:48.709 --> 19:52.843
[Grace whimpers]
Now I've been good, Grace.

19:52.887 --> 19:56.630
But, shh, shh, shh, shh.

19:56.673 --> 19:58.980
Don't scream.

19:59.023 --> 20:00.242
Think about your
father and what it

20:00.286 --> 20:03.071
would do to his ministry.

20:03.114 --> 20:06.205
I keep these church doors open.

20:06.248 --> 20:08.598
You know that this
church means everything

20:08.642 --> 20:11.122
to that daddy of yours.

20:11.166 --> 20:14.300
And all the money I
put into this church,

20:14.343 --> 20:17.216
you better believe I'ma take
back a little something for me.

20:17.259 --> 20:19.261
- Please.
- Shh.

20:19.305 --> 20:21.002
- Please don't.
- Ah, ah, don't.

20:21.045 --> 20:22.786
Shh shh shh.

20:22.830 --> 20:25.441
Don't scream, shh.

20:27.313 --> 20:31.404
[tense music]

20:53.164 --> 20:56.037
