- Oh.

27:54.977 --> 27:56.675
So you found us.
- I did.

27:56.718 --> 27:58.111
[laughing]

27:58.154 --> 27:59.416
And this is a
beautiful old house.

27:59.460 --> 28:01.157
- Oh, thank you.

28:01.201 --> 28:03.333
We inherited it from
a beautiful old woman

28:03.377 --> 28:04.987
who believed in our mission.

28:05.031 --> 28:07.207
It can be a lot to
keep up with, but,

28:07.250 --> 28:08.991
so grateful to have it.

28:09.035 --> 28:11.167
Hey come on, let introduce
you to my husband, Michael.

28:11.211 --> 28:11.994
It's right this way.
- Okay.

28:12.038 --> 28:14.649
- All right.

28:14.693 --> 28:16.303
Right this way.

28:17.304 --> 28:18.435
Michael.

28:19.610 --> 28:20.873
Michael?

28:20.916 --> 28:22.439
Music teacher's here.

28:22.483 --> 28:25.355
- Hey, nice to meet you.
[Kimberly chuckles]

28:25.399 --> 28:26.574
- Take a seat.

28:26.617 --> 28:28.010
I'll get you a cup of coffee.

28:28.054 --> 28:30.056
- Thank you, very much.

28:31.361 --> 28:32.972
- Uh, Q's getting out today.

28:33.015 --> 28:34.060
Reggie's gonna pick him up.

28:34.103 --> 28:35.539
- Perfect.

28:35.583 --> 28:38.325
[Michael sighs]

28:42.372 --> 28:43.765
- So a music teacher?

28:43.809 --> 28:44.723
- Yes.

28:48.465 --> 28:51.686
And here is my resume.

28:51.730 --> 28:52.992
There you are.

28:55.821 --> 28:58.693
- So what's your experience
working with troubled teens?

28:58.737 --> 29:00.434
- Define troubled teens.

29:00.477 --> 29:02.305
- I mean I'm assuming you
know what we do, right?

29:02.349 --> 29:03.654
- Well I viewed your website.

29:03.698 --> 29:04.917
Thank you.
- You're welcome.

29:04.960 --> 29:06.875
- And I've read your reviews.

29:06.919 --> 29:08.529
- You read reviews?

29:08.572 --> 29:10.096
And what was it exactly
that attracted you

29:10.139 --> 29:12.228
to our humble place? [chuckles]

29:12.272 --> 29:13.795
- Well I was under
the impression that

29:13.839 --> 29:16.276
your school needed my services.

29:16.319 --> 29:17.886
- We do.

29:17.930 --> 29:19.975
- I mean, it's not a school.

29:20.019 --> 29:22.064
Not in a traditional sense.

29:22.108 --> 29:24.458
Most of these kids
are repeat offenders.

29:24.501 --> 29:26.634
We're just trying to
teach 'em the right thing.

29:26.677 --> 29:29.593
It's about survival,
not academics.

29:29.637 --> 29:31.291
They need basic life skills.

29:31.334 --> 29:33.162
If we can give 'em that,
keep 'em off the streets,

29:33.206 --> 29:34.598
that's a win for us.

29:34.642 --> 29:36.035
That's the goal.

29:38.646 --> 29:41.170
[knocks]

29:41.214 --> 29:42.519
- Sam.

29:42.563 --> 29:44.478
Oh.

29:44.521 --> 29:46.219
Yep, come on, let's
get you cleaned up.

29:46.262 --> 29:47.742
Mhm, mhm.

29:47.786 --> 29:50.049
All right, right here.

29:50.092 --> 29:51.398
- Come on, man.

29:51.441 --> 29:53.400
- Here, here.

29:53.443 --> 29:56.229
Yep, keep puttin'
that pressure on it.

29:56.272 --> 29:57.970
You got it.

29:58.013 --> 30:01.887
- Like I said, life
skills. [chuckles]

30:01.930 --> 30:04.237
I mean, I'ma be
honest with you.

30:04.280 --> 30:06.326
Kimberly thought we
could use your help.

30:06.369 --> 30:09.242
Said we'd be blessed
to have you. [chuckles]

30:09.285 --> 30:11.810
- Oh, so you're saying that...

30:11.853 --> 30:13.246
- When can you start?

30:13.289 --> 30:15.117
- When would you
like me to start?

30:15.161 --> 30:16.815
- Today works.

30:16.858 --> 30:18.599
- Mr. Devlin, don't
you think that it would

30:18.642 --> 30:20.862
