right, thank you.

32:11.625 --> 32:13.018
- How do you do this?

32:13.061 --> 32:15.759
[sighs]

32:15.803 --> 32:17.761
- Okay, look.

32:17.805 --> 32:19.415
It takes some getting used to.

32:19.459 --> 32:20.939
But I promise you
that if you just--

32:20.982 --> 32:23.942
- This was a mistake.

32:23.985 --> 32:27.249
- The kids mean well, you just-

32:27.293 --> 32:31.297
- And you call this helping me.

32:31.340 --> 32:32.689
- Grace, please,
what can we do?

32:32.733 --> 32:36.041
- Nothing. I'm fine, thank you.

32:36.084 --> 32:38.521
- What? She said she's fine.

32:38.565 --> 32:41.350
Wait, wait, wait, wait, wait.

32:41.394 --> 32:44.397
Is it the schedule?

32:44.440 --> 32:46.399
- And you think this is funny?

32:46.442 --> 32:49.924
I have taught ambassador's
kids, and one time a prince.

32:49.968 --> 32:51.970
- Look, Jalen's
dad used to run one

32:52.013 --> 32:53.797
of the hardest
gangs on this block,

32:53.841 --> 32:57.453
so for real, for
real, we royalty too.

32:57.497 --> 32:59.760
You know my wife can make
a bad cup of coffee,

32:59.803 --> 33:01.109
but you aint have
to do all that.

33:01.153 --> 33:04.417
You could've just
thrown it away.

33:04.460 --> 33:06.767
They're kids, they're
gonna act out.

33:06.810 --> 33:08.508
I think someone from
where you're from,

33:08.551 --> 33:10.771
what is it, music
therapy, or whatever,

33:10.814 --> 33:14.427
would be more in tune with
how these at risk teens act.

33:14.470 --> 33:17.734
- My students have taught
kids from all over the world

33:17.778 --> 33:21.782
because of the skills
I knew to teach them,

33:21.825 --> 33:24.263
and you don't think I'm
qualified enough for you?

33:24.306 --> 33:26.743
- Paper says you qualified,
but it take way more

33:26.787 --> 33:28.049
than that to last.
- You don't have a schedule,

33:28.093 --> 33:30.834
you don't have curriculum.

33:30.878 --> 33:35.535
You, I'm assuming, don't
have money for supplies.

33:35.578 --> 33:38.059
- All the money goes to
the fancy universities

33:38.103 --> 33:39.713
like the one you came from.

33:39.756 --> 33:41.497
Look, we got a
saying around here:

33:41.541 --> 33:43.543
meet them where they are at.

33:43.586 --> 33:45.284
- And then?

33:45.327 --> 33:47.460
Because I'm pretty sure
I've already done that.

33:47.503 --> 33:48.896
- And that's it.

33:48.939 --> 33:51.507
Anything past
that is a calling.

33:51.551 --> 33:53.118
So where we goin'?

33:54.554 --> 33:57.339
[Grace scoffs]

33:58.558 --> 34:01.430
[birds chirping]

34:02.910 --> 34:04.520
Uh, hello?

34:06.435 --> 34:08.698
I'll get these.

34:08.742 --> 34:11.614
[birds chirping]

34:14.878 --> 34:18.012
- So we don't
usually have guests.

34:18.056 --> 34:20.580
Oh wow.

34:20.623 --> 34:24.236
I thought the kids had
it cleaned in here.

34:25.802 --> 34:26.934
[Grace coughs]
You know what,

34:26.977 --> 34:28.240
I could send some of them over.

34:28.283 --> 34:30.851
- No, that's fine. That's okay.

34:30.894 --> 34:32.331
- You sure?
- Mhm.

34:32.374 --> 34:34.246
- I really don't mind.

34:34.289 --> 34:36.335
I mean, they could clean up
some more, really, honestly.

34:36.378 --> 34:39.294
[Clears throat]

34:40.121 --> 34:42.558
Okay.

34:42.602 --> 34:46.345
Grace, I'm really
glad you're here.

34:46.388 --> 34:50.175
I think you'll be good
for us. [chuckles]

34:50.218 --> 34:51.350
Okay.

34:53.743 --> 34:55.397
All right.

34:55.441 --> 34:59.401
Well, get some rest.
Tomorrow's a new day.

34:59.445 --> 35:03.101
And again, thanks for
give us another shot.

35:05.494 --> 35:07.105
All right.

35:08.323 --> 35:10.760
