36:04.249 --> 36:07.687
Do the lyrics move
you in a certain way?

36:08.992 --> 36:11.212
What do you get from it?

36:11.256 --> 36:12.735
- It's not about what we get,

36:12.779 --> 36:14.781
it's about what we
don't have to get.

36:14.824 --> 36:18.219
Some of us don't wanna be
in our feelings all day.

36:18.263 --> 36:21.135
- So, music is the escape?

36:21.179 --> 36:23.529
- There's a lot worse
things than music.

36:23.572 --> 36:26.401
Uh, the people
you use to escape.

36:27.272 --> 36:28.360
- True.

36:28.403 --> 36:31.493
It's a healthy distraction.

36:31.537 --> 36:34.583
But on the other side of that,

36:34.627 --> 36:39.327
music can help us feel or
make sense of our emotions.

36:39.371 --> 36:43.157
- Like, for me, I,
I like listening to

36:43.201 --> 36:48.249
my favorite songs because
it makes me feel less alone.

36:48.293 --> 36:49.729
- So loneliness.

36:50.817 --> 36:52.384
What else?

36:52.427 --> 36:56.344
- Um, music is one of
the only things that

36:56.388 --> 36:59.869
doesn't ask for anything we
don't wanna give, I guess.

36:59.913 --> 37:01.741
- [Grace] How so?

37:01.784 --> 37:03.482
- We can listen to
it when we want to,

37:03.525 --> 37:05.397
turn it off when we don't
wanna hear it anymore.

37:05.440 --> 37:06.789
We can either get
something from it,

37:06.833 --> 37:09.139
or get nothing at
all, it just is.

37:09.183 --> 37:11.446
It lets us choose
how we wanna respond

37:11.490 --> 37:13.579
without telling
us how we should.

37:13.622 --> 37:15.363
I guess, I don't know.

37:15.407 --> 37:18.279
- That's pretty insightful.

37:18.323 --> 37:19.933
[scoffs]

37:19.976 --> 37:21.413
Do you disagree?

37:24.067 --> 37:26.331
- Just don't care.

37:26.374 --> 37:27.419
Just wondering
if there's a point

37:27.462 --> 37:29.377
to all of this or what?

37:29.421 --> 37:31.249
- Yo, chill.
- Please.

37:31.292 --> 37:34.077
Like y'all aint
wondering the same thing.

37:34.121 --> 37:35.775
This supposed to be
our time to kick back

37:35.818 --> 37:38.212
and not deal with somebody
else talking at us.

37:38.256 --> 37:41.259
- Well you know there have
been studies that suggest

37:41.302 --> 37:44.436
that babies in their
mother's wombs can hear

37:44.479 --> 37:46.742
and even recognize
the music that

37:46.786 --> 37:48.527
their mothers play for them.

37:48.570 --> 37:50.442
It can be a song, it
can be humming a song--

37:50.485 --> 37:52.531
- Don't talk to
me about my baby.

37:52.574 --> 37:54.881
- Look, I was just trying-
- That's your problem.

37:54.924 --> 37:57.449
Stop. Like, are you
even a real teacher?

37:57.492 --> 38:00.626
'Cause I aint heard
nothin' yet that matters.

38:00.669 --> 38:03.237
- [Grace] What
does matter to you?

38:03.281 --> 38:05.413
- Not this.

38:05.457 --> 38:07.807
- Well maybe not today,
but what about the future?

38:07.850 --> 38:09.417
[chuckles]

38:09.461 --> 38:13.029
That maybe later, one
day, what you learn

38:13.073 --> 38:16.076
here can impact your life.

38:16.119 --> 38:18.600
What you gonna do when
you leave this place,

38:18.644 --> 38:20.733
who you're going to be.

38:20.776 --> 38:25.912
A life outside of anything
you've ever known.

38:25.955 --> 38:30.917
Doing big things that you
never thought you could do.

38:30.960 --> 38:32.222
[scoffs]

38:32.266 --> 38:33.702
- Big?

38:33.746 --> 38:35.356
That aint us.

38:35.400 --> 38:38.011
We just trying to make
it through every day.

38:38.054 --> 38:39.752
- I can't even leave the house.

38:39.795 --> 38:42.624
- Look, Ms. Grace, was
it? We know our options.

38:42.668 --> 38:45.105
- Yup, and they suck.

38:46.541 --> 38:49.109
- Well then I've got
an important assignment

38:49.152 --> 38:50.937
for you to do tonight.
[Jaylen scoffs]

38:50.980 --> 38:52.460
- Wait, hold up, now she's
talking about assignment.

38:52.504 --> 38:54.201
Can someone please
tell this lady

38:54.244 --> 38:57.552
that we don't do homework here?

38:57.596 --> 39:00.250
- Facts.
- Yeah.

39:00.294 --> 39:01.904
- Are you telling me that
if I give you an assignment,

39:01.948 --> 39:05.255
you're not-
- No, no one would do it.

39:05.299 --> 39:08.084
I'm not trying to
be mean, but...

39:08.128 --> 39:10.652
- Not one of you
even wants to try?

39:10.696 --> 39:12.219
- I'm good.
- No.

39:12.262 --> 39:14.569
- You're just happy
doing nothing?

39:14.613 --> 39:16.832
- We do what we gotta
do to stay here.

39:16.876 --> 39:19.922
Why would we do
something we aint gotta?

39:19.966 --> 39:23.186
- Why indeed.

39:27.147 --> 39:30.019
[birds chirping]

39:34.459 --> 39:36.330
I did what you said.

39:36.374 --> 39:38.637
- Yeah?
- Yeah.

39:38.680 --> 39:41.161
But where they're
at is a problem.

39:41.204 --> 39:42.858
- Huh?

39:42.902 --> 39:45.731
- You told me to meet them
where they're at. I did.

39:45.774 --> 39:48.560
But where they're
at is a problem.

39:48.603 --> 39:51.911
- Oh, I see. See, I
thought we hired a teacher.

39:51.954 --> 39:54.043
But it seems like we
just hired a judge.

39:54.087 --> 39:57.090
- No, what you did
was hire the sitter.

39:57.133 --> 39:58.744
That's what this is.

39:58.787 --> 40:00.354
- Look, I don't have
time to give you

40:00.398 --> 40:02.356
a pep talk every time
something happens.

40:02.400 --> 40:04.271
It's the job.

40:04.314 --> 40:06.752
First it was too hard for you,
now it's too easy for you.

40:06.795 --> 40:08.928
What do you want?

40:08.971 --> 40:12.279
- I want to help.
- Well then help.

40:16.762 --> 40:18.372
- I mean I'll trade you this-
- Look, I'm just saying,

40:18.416 --> 40:19.939
then keep your door closed.

40:19.982 --> 40:21.897
- Hey, if I wanna leave
my door open, it's open.

40:21.941 --> 40:23.203
[laughing]

40:23.246 --> 40:24.639
- Hey.

40:24.683 --> 40:27.642
- Are we having a sleep over?

40:27.686 --> 40:29.035
- [Q] Come on with
your big head.

40:29.078 --> 40:30.645
- You can't talk
for nobody, dog.

40:30.689 --> 40:33.213
Have you seen that
thing you carry around?

40:33.256 --> 40:35.433
- Will you be joining us?

40:37.478 --> 40:39.567
Is everyone comfortable?

40:39.611 --> 40:41.917
- Of course.
- I could use another pillow.

40:41.961 --> 40:43.745
- Shut up.
- Yeah.

40:43.789 --> 40:45.486
Yeah. [laughs]

40:45.530 --> 40:47.096
- I'll catch one.

40:47.140 --> 40:49.272
[laughing]

40:49.316 --> 40:55.235
- Yes, this is really nice.

40:55.278 --> 40:56.932
Ah.

40:58.630 --> 41:02.590
And to think, I was
worried about what

41:02.634 --> 41:04.897
you all thought about me.

41:04.940 --> 41:07.421
[Grace chuckles]

41:07.465 --> 41:12.905
Racking my brain with what
I could do to help you,

41:12.948 --> 41:17.257
or where I would go
if I decided to leave.

41:17.300 --> 41:20.608
And then it finally
occurred to me:

41:20.652 --> 41:26.571
I don't have to think about
any of this stuff. [laughs]

41:26.614 --> 41:27.920
- She's loosing it.

41:27.963 --> 41:32.968
- Not if I have one
of those passes.

41:33.012 --> 41:36.406
Oh, you know what
I'm talking about?

41:36.450 --> 41:39.540
Because you all have
them, the passes.

41:39.584 --> 41:41.934
- We don't have any passes?

41:41.977 --> 41:44.980
- Oh, I'm not
gonna tell anybody.

41:45.024 --> 41:47.940
Just tell me where
you got the passes.

41:47.983 --> 41:50.551
- We stole 'em.
[laughing]

41:50.595 --> 41:52.510
- Um, passes for what?

41:53.467 --> 41:55.469
- The passes on life.

41:55.513 --> 41:59.299
The free passes that
say that all you

41:59.342 --> 42:03.390
have to do is show up
and that's good enough.

42:03.433 --> 42:08.438
The passes that say you
don't have to do the work.

42:08.482 --> 42:12.660
You talk a tough game.

42:12.704 --> 42:16.577
And you almost had
me for a minute.

42:16.621 --> 42:19.493
You intimidate and
you make your threats

42:19.537 --> 42:21.539
and you demand respect.

42:23.758 --> 42:26.761
But when it comes time to
stand up for yourselves,

42:26.805 --> 42:29.024
you throw up your
hands and you back into

42:29.068 --> 42:32.332
the corner and you cry
and you oh, I'm scared,

42:32.375 --> 42:35.378
I can't do this, it's too hard.

42:35.422 --> 42:36.815
- We know how to fight.
- Yeah.

42:36.858 --> 42:38.468
- No you don't.

42:38.512 --> 42:40.601
Not for yourselves.

42:40.645 --> 42:43.822
Now, you may have
been victimized.

42:43.865 --> 42:45.780
No fault of your own.

42:45.824 --> 42:52.439
And you may not have family,
friends, a $1.50 to your name.

42:52.482 --> 42:56.356
But you do have something,
something so powerful

42:56.399 --> 43:01.230
that no one can ever
take away from you.

43:01.274 --> 43:03.232
- What's that? Our
court records, right?

43:03.276 --> 43:04.277
[laughing]

43:04.320 --> 43:07.497
- [Grace] Choice.

43:07.541 --> 43:12.067
- Most of us were sent
here. It wasn't our choice.

43:12.111 --> 43:14.461
- That's not how it
is for most of us.

43:14.504 --> 43:17.464
Even if we wanna move on,

43:17.507 --> 43:20.293
the world doesn't
just let you forget.

43:20.336 --> 43:24.079
- But you still have a choice,

43:24.123 --> 43:28.083
to not let it define one
more moment of your lives.

43:28.127 --> 43:30.695
Just stop believing
the lies that this

43:30.738 --> 43:32.653
is all that there is.

43:32.697 --> 43:37.266
You stand up and fight. Stand
up and fight for yourselves!

43:38.790 --> 43:41.619
[sighs]

43:41.662 --> 43:43.403
Now...

43:45.623 --> 43:51.106
You, you, you can just give up.

43:51.150 --> 43:57.809
You can let the world, and
all of the bad people in it,

43:57.852 --> 44:01.682
determine your
future, and this class

44:01.726 --> 44:04.467
will be your nap time.

44:04.511 --> 44:08.428
But if you decide to
stand up for yourselves,

44:10.604 --> 44:13.520
stand up and fight
for yourselves

44:13.563 --> 44:19.482
and do something positive
with all of that negativity,

44:19.526 --> 44:25.663
all of that pain,
you just let me know.

44:27.186 --> 44:32.321
Now my future is good, no
matter what you decide.

44:33.932 --> 44:36.499
[soft music]

44:39.372 --> 44:44.507
You just let me know.
[soft music]

44:51.906 --> 44:53.081
Yes.

44:54.648 --> 44:56.432
This is good.

44:56.476 --> 44:58.608
- You said what?
- Michael.

44:58.652 --> 45:01.002
- If we only expect
the minimum from them,

45:01.046 --> 45:02.743
that is all we're going to get.

45:02.787 --> 45:04.527
And then they will never,
ever know that they

45:04.571 --> 45:06.573
are capable of so much more.

45:06.616 --> 45:08.183
- Now she's telling
me how to do my job.

45:08.227 --> 45:10.055
Unbelievable.

45:10.098 --> 45:12.361
You don't just walk up
in somebody house, Grace,

45:12.405 --> 45:14.320
and start telling
them how to clean it.

45:14.363 --> 45:18.367
- I didn't just walk in.
I was invited to stay.

45:18.411 --> 45:21.588
- Exactly. Key word:
"invited".

45:21.631 --> 45:23.416
I should've let
you walk that day.

45:23.459 --> 45:26.419
- Michael!
- Then why didn't you?

45:26.462 --> 45:27.899
[Michael sighs]

45:27.942 --> 45:29.335
- Look.

45:31.424 --> 45:33.078
I know these kids.

45:33.121 --> 45:35.733
I know what it's like
to be one of these kids.

45:35.776 --> 45:37.909
They don't call 'em
at risk for nothin'.

45:37.952 --> 45:39.737
Last thing they need is
somebody coming in here

45:39.780 --> 45:42.783
sellin' 'em dreams,
tellin' 'em more lies,

45:42.827 --> 45:44.524
leading to more disappointment.

45:44.567 --> 45:48.571
- Everybody's at risk of
something, Mr. Devlin.

45:48.615 --> 45:50.225
That's life.

45:50.269 --> 45:52.532
But we just can't, we
can't grow complacent

45:52.575 --> 45:54.752
and not try to do better.

45:55.796 --> 45:57.450
- Oh, I get it.

45:57.493 --> 45:58.712
This some of that old
recovery talk, aint it?

45:58.756 --> 46:00.496
What are you, 90
days clean now?

46:00.540 --> 46:02.063
- Okay, Michael,
that is enough.

46:02.107 --> 46:03.891
What has gotten into you?

46:03.935 --> 46:06.241
You of all people
should know better.

46:06.285 --> 46:08.287
Okay, this house would
not be in existence

46:08.330 --> 46:10.332
if you just settled
for less and stopped

46:10.376 --> 46:14.510
fighting for more, for
yourself and the kids.

46:14.554 --> 46:16.164
Now I wanna show
Grace their files.

46:16.208 --> 46:17.818
- No.

46:17.862 --> 46:18.863
- At least she'd know
where we started from.

46:18.906 --> 46:20.386
- They're private. No!

46:20.429 --> 46:22.344
- So, she could just-
- Mr. Devlin.

46:22.388 --> 46:24.433
You, you've have a
problem with me from the

46:24.477 --> 46:28.046
moment I stepped inside your
door and I don't know why,

46:28.089 --> 46:31.223
but honestly, I don't care.

46:31.266 --> 46:34.226
Because at this
point in my life,

46:34.269 --> 46:39.144
I am done with trying
to please people.

46:39.187 --> 46:44.366
And 115 days sober,
if you must know.

46:45.280 --> 46:47.239
And you're my boss.

46:47.282 --> 46:51.809
And I can respect and accept
that this is your house.

46:53.114 --> 46:56.639
- Well?
- But you gave me those kids.

46:56.683 --> 47:00.165
You stuck me in
the room with them,

47:00.208 --> 47:02.689
and as long as I'm living here,

47:02.732 --> 47:05.648
I refuse to let
my room be a mess.

47:07.433 --> 47:10.871
- Look, you two work this out.

47:10.915 --> 47:12.786
But when it all
comes falling apart,

47:12.830 --> 47:15.267
and these kids end
up spittin' bullets,

47:15.310 --> 47:17.573
you better hope to God you got
something real to give 'em.

47:17.617 --> 47:24.102
[clattering]

47:28.846 --> 47:31.022
[knocking]

47:31.065 --> 47:33.763
- Come in.

47:38.420 --> 47:41.510
- This aint me backin' down.

47:41.554 --> 47:45.297
- So you trust me, then?
- Trust might be pushin' it,

47:45.340 --> 47:47.299
but I respect your
assertiveness.

47:47.342 --> 47:49.954
It's not everyday I come across
someone as aggressive as me.

47:49.997 --> 47:51.738
[Grace chuckles]

47:51.781 --> 47:55.873
- Look, I don't wanna hurt
these kids, Mr. Devlin.

47:55.916 --> 47:58.484
[soft music]

48:03.054 --> 48:07.188
- Two years ago, they
sent us a 13-year-old boy.

48:07.232 --> 48:09.930
He couldn't speak,
he stared at walls,

48:09.974 --> 48:12.367
he wet the bed, he
couldn't even feed himself.

48:12.411 --> 48:15.283
13-years-old.

48:15.327 --> 48:17.546
And it's not like he couldn't.

48:17.590 --> 48:18.808
You look at his
early school records,

48:18.852 --> 48:21.202
it shows that he
was a smart kid.

48:21.246 --> 48:25.119
But whatever happened to
him at his parent's house?

48:25.163 --> 48:27.948
Completely checked out.

48:27.992 --> 48:30.255
The therapists and
all their credentials,

48:30.298 --> 48:32.431
they told us to keep pushin'
him, keep pushin' him,

48:32.474 --> 48:33.998
don't go easy on him.

48:34.041 --> 48:37.262
They said if we did,
he'd never recover.

48:37.305 --> 48:40.178
You can't argue with these
doctors, so that's what we did.

48:40.221 --> 48:43.964
For a year straight, all we
did was focus on results.

48:44.008 --> 48:46.227
No visible sign of success.

48:46.271 --> 48:48.229
You know what they
told us to do?

48:48.273 --> 48:49.752
Just get rid of him.

48:49.796 --> 48:52.755
Just like that,
just get rid of him.

48:54.018 --> 48:56.977
Couldn't do it.
Couldn't do it.

48:57.021 --> 48:58.979
I don't care if he
decided to check out

48:59.023 --> 49:03.679
the rest of his life, all we
were called to do was love him.

49:03.723 --> 49:06.769
Dirty, smelly,
exhausting, whatever.

49:07.988 --> 49:09.250
Just love him.

49:10.730 --> 49:22.785
- And what happened?
[soft music]

49:27.399 --> 49:30.837
You've got a good heart.

49:30.880 --> 49:34.493
- Just bring me these
back in the morning.

49:35.320 --> 49:38.410
[soft music]

49:43.067 --> 49:51.466
[soft music]

49:55.993 --> 50:01.955
♪ I've been searching
my entire life ♪

50:01.999 --> 50:06.612
♪ To be seen and
to be recognized ♪

50:06.655 --> 50:09.876
♪ And after all I
put myself through ♪

50:09.919 --> 50:15.882
♪ The only thing I had
to do to find you ♪

50:15.925 --> 50:18.580
♪ Was open up my eyes

50:18.624 --> 50:21.714
♪ You see who I am

50:21.757 --> 50:24.978
♪ Even when I don't see it

50:25.022 --> 50:27.763
♪ You see what I can't

50:27.807 --> 50:30.505
♪ And I always
know you mean it ♪

50:30.549 --> 50:32.768
♪ When you speak to
my heart, to my soul ♪

50:32.812 --> 50:37.904
♪ And I know you love
me right where I stand ♪

50:37.947 --> 50:40.907
♪ You see who I am

50:40.950 --> 50:42.561
♪ You see who

50:42.604 --> 50:45.259
- If this is what you
want me to do, God,

50:47.783 --> 50:50.221
please give me the strength.

50:53.441 --> 50:59.665
[soft music]

51:36.441 --> 51:37.920
- Hey, wake her up.

51:37.964 --> 51:39.922
- You wake her up.

51:39.966 --> 51:40.923
- Okay.

51:43.274 --> 51:44.753
- Um, Ms. Grace?

51:49.367 --> 51:50.629
Get the pillows.

51:50.672 --> 51:54.285
- Yeah, let's go.
[soft music]

51:56.113 --> 51:57.679
[laughing]

51:57.723 --> 51:59.333
- Ay yo, Quentin?

51:59.377 --> 52:00.291
Take this.

52:03.990 --> 52:05.731
Give me the chair.

52:05.774 --> 52:06.732
Scoot.

52:08.125 --> 52:13.608
[soft music]

52:18.309 --> 52:20.833
- What?

52:20.876 --> 52:25.794
Y'all can do what y'all want.
It's your choice, remember?

52:25.838 --> 52:28.275
[soft music]

52:28.319 --> 52:29.450
- Well?

52:31.670 --> 52:33.846
- Um, before we
like, start and all,

52:33.889 --> 52:36.936
we just had a quick
question first.

52:37.806 --> 52:39.112
[sighs]

52:39.156 --> 52:40.809
You're not gonna
make us like, sing,

52:40.853 --> 52:42.550
like we're in a choir
or anything, right?

52:42.594 --> 52:43.769
- Do you wanna start a choir?

52:43.812 --> 52:45.379
- [Jalen] I'm good, bruh, no.

52:45.423 --> 52:46.554
- I've heard Selina
sing in the shower--

52:46.598 --> 52:48.774
- No.
- You can't sing.

52:48.817 --> 52:50.384
- Oh, whoa, whoa, whoa.

52:50.428 --> 52:53.561
It's okay, it's
okay, no, no choir.

52:53.605 --> 52:54.519
No choir.

52:56.129 --> 52:57.957
- [Jalen] All right.

52:59.611 --> 53:07.401
[soft vocalizing]
[insects buzzing]

53:12.101 --> 53:14.800
♪ Lullaby

53:14.843 --> 53:19.021
♪ Lullaby

53:19.065 --> 53:22.242
♪ Lullaby, lullaby

53:22.286 --> 53:26.028
♪ Lullaby, mama's baby

53:26.072 --> 53:28.770
♪ Lullaby, lullaby

53:28.814 --> 53:32.296
♪ Lullaby and good night

53:32.339 --> 53:36.082
♪ Lullaby, lullaby

53:36.125 --> 53:40.129
♪ Lullaby mama's baby

53:40.173 --> 53:45.265
♪ Lullaby, lullaby, lullaby

53:45.309 --> 53:47.963
♪ Sleep tight

53:50.227 --> 53:59.192
[soft music]
[insects buzzing]

54:03.805 --> 54:06.025
- [Jalen] And that, my
friends, is a solid jam.

54:06.068 --> 54:07.766
Personal opinion.
- That was good.

54:07.809 --> 54:09.158
- Thank you.

54:09.202 --> 54:11.030
I think anything
before 2010 is solid.

54:11.073 --> 54:12.901
- Facts.
- They're throwbacks, yeah.

54:12.945 --> 54:14.555
- All right, so who is next?

54:14.599 --> 54:16.035
- [Sam] I, actually?

54:16.078 --> 54:17.558
- Really?
- Yeah, yeah, yeah, come on.

54:17.602 --> 54:19.430
- [Jalen] All right,
let's get it, man.

54:19.473 --> 54:22.084
- [Tay] This is
gonna be interesting.

54:22.128 --> 54:23.695
- [Jalen] No, it's not trash.

54:23.738 --> 54:25.174
- That's why your phone
felt it was trash.

54:25.218 --> 54:25.914
- [Jalen] You know
what? You're trash.

54:25.958 --> 54:27.089
- Okay.

54:27.133 --> 54:28.874
[girl vocalizing]

54:28.917 --> 54:30.441
♪ Lullaby, lullaby

54:30.484 --> 54:32.834
- Turn it off.
♪ Lullaby, lullaby

54:32.878 --> 54:33.574
What the is
wrong with you?

54:33.618 --> 54:34.401
- Daniella!

54:34.445 --> 54:35.794
- Yo.

54:35.837 --> 54:37.535
- You asked us to play a song.

54:37.578 --> 54:39.363
It's a great song,
I don't know why-

54:39.406 --> 54:41.930
- Can't you ever just stay
out of people's business?

54:41.974 --> 54:44.672
- Daniella, I have tried to be
tolerant with your attitude,

54:44.716 --> 54:46.761
but the moment you put
your hands on someone else,

54:46.805 --> 54:48.328
that is enough!

54:48.372 --> 54:49.547
Now, you wanna be left alone?

54:49.590 --> 54:51.549
You wanna sit in your misery?

54:51.592 --> 54:53.855
Fine, but you're gonna
do it somewhere else.

54:53.899 --> 54:56.118
Go, go, get out.

54:56.162 --> 54:59.905
We're perfectly fine
here without you. Go.

55:01.950 --> 55:04.301
- I'll deal with you later.

55:05.563 --> 55:06.868
- Sam?
- Yeah, no, mm-mm.

55:06.912 --> 55:08.000
- Sweetie.

55:08.043 --> 55:09.436
Come on, come on, come on.

55:09.480 --> 55:10.437
- [Kimberly] We knew
this could end up

55:10.481 --> 55:12.134
causing problems for us.

55:12.178 --> 55:13.353
- [Michael] I don't
even know why they care.

55:13.397 --> 55:14.485
[Kimberly sighs]

55:14.528 --> 55:15.921
- [Kimberly] What should we do?

55:15.964 --> 55:17.139
- [Michael] They
don't want her here.

55:17.183 --> 55:18.793
They don't want her anywhere.

55:18.837 --> 55:20.534
- [Kimberly] So should
we say something now?

55:20.578 --> 55:23.102
- [Michael] I'll figure it out.

55:23.145 --> 55:26.975
- I'm sorry, but today she
really crossed the line.

55:27.019 --> 55:30.370
If you would've seen the
look on Sam's face...

55:30.414 --> 55:33.721
- What is she talking about?

55:33.765 --> 55:35.810
You two figure it out.

55:35.854 --> 55:37.290
[Kimberly sighs]

55:37.334 --> 55:38.247
- Grace.

55:39.292 --> 55:42.774
[Kimberly sighs]

55:42.817 --> 55:46.343
We're having problems
with our organization.

55:46.386 --> 55:49.041
Daniella's case worker
is harassing her.

55:49.084 --> 55:50.521
They think they
should send Daniella

55:50.564 --> 55:53.262
to another facility
to have her baby.

55:53.306 --> 55:55.787
- And that's a bad thing?
- Yes.

55:55.830 --> 55:57.005
The place they're
trying to send her to

55:57.049 --> 55:58.267
only cares about the funding.

55:58.311 --> 56:00.661
The kids? They don't matter.

56:00.705 --> 56:02.271
And I hate to say this,
but, she'd be better off

56:02.315 --> 56:04.578
at home than at that place.

56:04.622 --> 56:07.407
Conditions alone are
just, they're horrible.

56:07.451 --> 56:10.584
- Well don't you have a say?

56:10.628 --> 56:13.500
- Majority of our funding
comes from the organization.

56:13.544 --> 56:17.069
We do what we love,
or what they say goes.

56:17.112 --> 56:19.898
- And if you refuse?
[Kimberly sighs]

56:19.941 --> 56:22.509
- We lose everything.

56:22.553 --> 56:24.424
I mean, we went against
them once before with Sam

56:24.468 --> 56:27.209
and they're still
holding it against us.

56:27.253 --> 56:31.649
Lucky for everyone, Sam
recovered, but had he not...

56:33.955 --> 56:37.002
- Does Daniella know?

56:37.045 --> 56:42.050
- Michael will be telling her.
[melancholy music]

56:44.749 --> 56:47.708
[beat boxing]

56:47.752 --> 56:51.669
♪ Got a bowl of fruit,
got a bowl of fruit ♪

56:51.712 --> 56:53.366
- Hey, how come
you didn't tell me

56:53.410 --> 56:55.629
you could write like that?

56:55.673 --> 56:59.416
- Um, I was just
following directions.

56:59.459 --> 57:02.070
- Oh, it was poetry, Jalen.

57:02.114 --> 57:04.986
Now you've got a real talent.

57:05.030 --> 57:07.467
Do you ever read what
you write for people?

57:07.511 --> 57:09.426
[chuckles]
- Last time I read

57:09.469 --> 57:13.430
something I wrote for
somebody, um, was my mom.

57:13.473 --> 57:14.866
And she slapped
me across the face

57:14.909 --> 57:16.607
and told me to get the
out of her room,

57:16.650 --> 57:18.347
so that tells you how
that went. [chuckles]

57:18.391 --> 57:20.088
- Well if I promise
you that that

57:20.132 --> 57:24.310
won't happen in my class,
would you consider it?

57:24.353 --> 57:25.442
- You really think
it's that good, huh?

57:25.485 --> 57:27.313
- Oh, it is that good.

57:29.620 --> 57:30.795
- I guess.

57:30.838 --> 57:33.275
Nah. Not really, I don't know.

57:33.319 --> 57:36.540
- So you will, or
you won't, or you...

57:38.150 --> 57:39.891
- Probably not.
Yeah, I don't know.

57:39.934 --> 57:40.848
Excuse me.

57:44.678 --> 57:46.593
- "Lift up your eyes
and look around.

57:46.637 --> 57:49.553
"All your children
gather and come to you."

57:49.596 --> 57:52.512
- "As surely as I live,
declares the Lord,

57:52.556 --> 57:55.254
"you will wear them
all as ornaments.

57:55.297 --> 57:58.431
"You will put them
on like a bride."

58:00.215 --> 58:02.609
I never realized
until this moment

58:02.653 --> 58:05.307
the significance of that
scripture and how it's

58:05.351 --> 58:07.962
playing out right
here in our own lives.

58:09.442 --> 58:11.618
Michael and I have
been trying to have

58:11.662 --> 58:16.971
a child of our
own for years now,

58:17.015 --> 58:21.541
and uh, for whatever reason,
it just hasn't happened.

58:24.457 --> 58:28.592
I went through a phase
where I blamed God,

58:28.635 --> 58:33.031
where I doubted he
cared and I was angry.

58:33.074 --> 58:36.469
I was angry at him,
at Michael, at myself,

58:36.513 --> 58:39.559
for daring to hope.

58:39.603 --> 58:45.652
But uh, these verses
really hit me today.

58:48.350 --> 58:51.702
So maybe I don't have
a child of my own.

58:51.745 --> 58:55.619
I've got something
just as powerful.

59:00.319 --> 59:04.323
All of you.
[soft piano music]

59:06.107 --> 59:08.370
[laughs]

59:12.984 --> 59:14.159
- [Man] That's right-

59:14.202 --> 59:15.595
- You're not listening to me.

59:15.639 --> 59:16.683
- [Man] Your baby,
keep your baby.

59:16.727 --> 59:18.337
- No.
- Keep it.

59:18.380 --> 59:19.904
I don't even care if
you're gonna be trash,

59:19.947 --> 59:21.166
just like your mother.

59:21.209 --> 59:22.602
I hope you don't
end up homeless.

59:22.646 --> 59:24.082
If you do, it's
not my problem.

59:24.125 --> 59:27.433
That's your--
[Hung up call]

59:32.133 --> 59:32.917
[Daniella sighs]

59:32.960 --> 59:35.223
- Figures.

59:35.267 --> 59:36.747
What?

59:39.053 --> 59:42.013
You always got
somethin' to say.

59:42.056 --> 59:44.406
Let's hear it.

59:44.450 --> 59:49.281
What wisdom do you have
for us today, Ms. Grace?

59:49.324 --> 59:53.154
- Are you okay?
[soft music]

59:54.155 --> 59:56.201
Is he the father?

59:56.244 --> 59:59.247
- It's between him
and four others.

1:00:00.248 --> 1:00:02.381
It's a joke.

1:00:06.254 --> 1:00:10.258
He just doesn't wanna
be the father, but,

1:00:10.302 --> 1:00:12.086
I know I shouldn't
call him.

1:00:12.130 --> 1:00:15.263
I just thought maybe...

1:00:17.962 --> 1:00:19.790
I don't know.

1:00:19.833 --> 1:00:22.009
It doesn't matter.

1:00:24.359 --> 1:00:27.711
You hear that they're
making me leave?

1:00:29.103 --> 1:00:31.062
I'm not going to that place.

1:00:31.105 --> 1:00:35.457
I don't care if I end up in a
box behind a gas station, bro,

1:00:35.501 --> 1:00:38.417
I'm not lettin' them
do this to me again.

1:00:38.460 --> 1:00:39.723
- Kimberly and Michael,
they're doing everything

1:00:39.766 --> 1:00:43.465
that they can to keep you here.

1:00:43.509 --> 1:00:47.905
- My mom keeps hitting me up,
telling me I can come home,

1:00:47.948 --> 1:00:50.734
that she'll help me
take care of the baby.

1:00:50.777 --> 1:00:52.866
- Help is good.

1:00:52.910 --> 1:00:56.696
- I know what kind
of help she is.

1:00:56.740 --> 1:01:01.309
I won't let my daughter
grow up around that woman.

1:01:01.353 --> 1:01:02.920
- A daughter.

1:01:02.963 --> 1:01:04.617
- Yeah, it's kind of
crazy what she's gonna

1:01:04.661 --> 1:01:08.490
have to go through just
'cause of who she is.

1:01:08.534 --> 1:01:11.929
What I'm gonna have
to protect her from,

1:01:11.972 --> 1:01:14.235
as if I don't have
my own problems.

1:01:14.279 --> 1:01:17.586
- You're not worthless,
and you're not crazy,

1:01:17.630 --> 1:01:19.588
and you are not trash.

1:01:20.546 --> 1:01:22.679
- What if I am?

1:01:22.722 --> 1:01:24.898
You don't know me.

1:01:24.942 --> 1:01:28.380
Look, I don't need
you to pretend.

1:01:28.423 --> 1:01:33.864
I keep it straight and I expect
other people to do the same.

1:01:33.907 --> 1:01:36.910
- You're rude, and
you don't have respect

1:01:36.954 --> 1:01:39.434
for anyone I've seen so far,

1:01:39.478 --> 1:01:42.481
because you don't have
respect for yourself.

1:01:42.524 --> 1:01:43.787
Crazy? No.

1:01:43.830 --> 1:01:44.962
Trash? No.

1:01:45.005 --> 1:01:48.139
And certainly not worthless.

1:01:49.967 --> 1:01:51.882
- I won't bother you again.

1:01:51.925 --> 1:01:54.232
I can take care of myself.

1:01:58.540 --> 1:02:04.677
[soft piano music]

1:02:22.956 --> 1:02:25.742
- Yes.

1:02:30.398 --> 1:02:32.009
Yes.

1:02:34.881 --> 1:02:36.535
Thank you.

1:02:37.754 --> 1:02:42.846
[soft piano music]

1:03:06.957 --> 1:03:10.525
[soft piano music]

1:03:10.569 --> 1:03:14.791
♪ You're all I need

1:03:14.834 --> 1:03:19.752
♪ To make this life
of mine ♪

1:03:19.796 --> 1:03:26.890
♪ More than complete

1:03:29.196 --> 1:03:31.372
♪ Oh

1:03:34.201 --> 1:03:35.333
- Well there you have it.

1:03:35.376 --> 1:03:36.900
All right.
[clapping]

1:03:36.943 --> 1:03:39.337
- Girl just take us to church.
[laughing]

1:03:39.380 --> 1:03:40.599
[Selina speaks in
Spanish]

1:03:40.642 --> 1:03:42.253
- No, no, no, no, no.

1:03:42.296 --> 1:03:45.256
You shouldn't sneak
up on me like that.

1:03:45.299 --> 1:03:46.648
Come on in, come on in.
- What's all this, Ms. Grace?

1:03:46.692 --> 1:03:48.041
- Just come on in.
- Ms. Grace,

1:03:48.085 --> 1:03:50.783
you promised us no choir.
- Hey, no choir.

1:03:50.827 --> 1:03:52.437
Just instruments.

1:03:52.480 --> 1:03:54.221
Come on in, come come,
come see what we have.

1:03:54.265 --> 1:03:55.701
See what we have.
- Are you serious?

1:03:55.744 --> 1:03:58.008
- Yes I am serious.
I am very serious.

1:03:58.051 --> 1:03:59.836
Absolutely.
- If you say so. [laughs]

1:03:59.879 --> 1:04:02.447
- Let me try this one.

1:04:02.490 --> 1:04:04.797
- Now, just pick it up.

1:04:04.841 --> 1:04:08.105
- Oh my gosh, it's so heavy.
- Yes, yes, yes, yes, yes.

1:04:08.148 --> 1:04:09.846
And just-
- And I hold it like this?

1:04:09.889 --> 1:04:12.152
- Absolutely. Absolutely.
[soft guitar strumming]

1:04:12.196 --> 1:04:13.110
- Hey.

1:04:14.502 --> 1:04:15.939
- You look really
dumb with that.

1:04:15.982 --> 1:04:20.291
- Thanks. I appreciate
it. [chuckles]

1:04:20.334 --> 1:04:22.206
You know, I bet you have
a really nice smile.

1:04:22.249 --> 1:04:24.425
Too bad nobody gets to see it.

1:04:24.469 --> 1:04:25.600
- Yeah, well you
don't have to put

1:04:25.644 --> 1:04:27.298
up with me for much longer.

1:04:27.341 --> 1:04:30.867
- Yeah, and why is that?
- They're sending me away.

1:04:30.910 --> 1:04:32.520
- Wait, seriously?

1:04:32.564 --> 1:04:34.696
Who? Michael
and Kimberly?

1:04:34.740 --> 1:04:37.090
- Social workers.

1:04:37.134 --> 1:04:40.180
- I mean, where
are you going? Why?

1:04:43.183 --> 1:04:44.576
Did they at least
tell you when?

1:04:44.619 --> 1:04:46.708
- I don't know.

1:04:46.752 --> 1:04:48.232
Could be any day, I guess.

1:04:48.275 --> 1:04:49.668
[scoffs]

1:04:49.711 --> 1:04:51.626
- Nah, if it was
me, I'd be trippin'.

1:04:51.670 --> 1:04:55.587
I mean like, we bump heads, I
mean, but this is your home.

1:04:55.630 --> 1:04:57.502
Your family.

1:04:57.545 --> 1:05:00.418
- People are the same
no matter where you go.

1:05:00.461 --> 1:05:01.898
- I mean, how would you know?

1:05:01.941 --> 1:05:03.247
You never gave any
of us a chance.

1:05:03.290 --> 1:05:05.249
- Yeah, and now
I don't have to.

1:05:05.292 --> 1:05:07.599
Why you always gotta make
everything so personal?

1:05:07.642 --> 1:05:08.992
- It' snot even like that.

1:05:09.035 --> 1:05:10.732
- I shouldn't even
have told you.

1:05:10.776 --> 1:05:11.820
- Aye, wait a second,
we could talk this out.

1:05:11.864 --> 1:05:13.431
It's not that..
serious.

1:05:15.781 --> 1:05:17.609
[sighs]

1:05:17.652 --> 1:05:21.004
[teenagers chattering]

1:05:23.267 --> 1:05:27.010
[soft music]
[birds chirping]

1:05:27.053 --> 1:05:28.228
- Listen y'all, we've
been noticing a lot of

1:05:28.272 --> 1:05:30.404
holes in the walls around here.

1:05:30.448 --> 1:05:33.364
Anybody wanna own up to that?

1:05:33.407 --> 1:05:35.148
- It was the lizard?

1:05:35.192 --> 1:05:38.586
- Aye, no snitchin'.
- Yeah, that's what I thought.

1:05:38.630 --> 1:05:40.153
Anyway, Daniella?

1:05:41.850 --> 1:05:45.724
Any thoughts or concerns
over the pregnancy?

1:05:45.767 --> 1:05:48.596
- I mean, I'm not
exactly looking forward

1:05:48.640 --> 1:05:51.295
to pushing a head out of-
- No, I think we got it.

1:05:51.338 --> 1:05:54.124
- So we're just not gonna
talk about the situation?

1:05:54.167 --> 1:05:55.734
What are y'all doin'
to stop this, huh?

1:05:55.777 --> 1:05:57.344
How is she supposed
to prepare for a baby

1:05:57.388 --> 1:05:59.216
if she doesn't know
where she's gonna be?

1:05:59.259 --> 1:06:00.957
- You're right.

1:06:01.000 --> 1:06:04.003
We're all family, and if
anything has the potential

1:06:04.047 --> 1:06:07.398
to affect one of us, it
should affect all of us.

1:06:07.441 --> 1:06:09.313
But we're doing everything
we can to make sure

1:06:09.356 --> 1:06:11.315
Daniella does not
leave this house.

1:06:11.358 --> 1:06:12.751
- That's right.

1:06:13.926 --> 1:06:15.797
- What does she do?

1:06:15.841 --> 1:06:18.496
Mike, I've been locked
up how many times?

1:06:18.539 --> 1:06:20.411
I literally broke
into someone's house.

1:06:20.454 --> 1:06:23.153
- Q.
- No, I'm on house arrest.

1:06:23.196 --> 1:06:24.545
- Okay.
- No one's kicking me out.

1:06:24.589 --> 1:06:26.983
- Q, listen. She
didn't do anything.

1:06:27.026 --> 1:06:28.027
It's her case workers,
okay?

1:06:28.071 --> 1:06:29.420
They just, they-

1:06:31.813 --> 1:06:34.207
They just want what's
best for her and the baby.

1:06:34.251 --> 1:06:35.382
[Jaylen scoffs]

1:06:35.426 --> 1:06:37.036
- By sending me to Heflin Hall?

1:06:37.080 --> 1:06:39.560
- Look, I don't
even like Daniella.

1:06:39.604 --> 1:06:41.736
But I wouldn't want
her to go there.

1:06:41.780 --> 1:06:42.999
The place is bad.

1:06:43.042 --> 1:06:45.610
- I thought we were safe here.

1:06:47.220 --> 1:06:48.961
And now you're
telling me that we

1:06:49.005 --> 1:06:51.007
can get thrown out just
by doing nothin' wrong?

1:06:51.050 --> 1:06:52.356
- See that's why I
aint wanna say nothin'.

1:06:52.399 --> 1:06:54.271
Aint no point of
getting all worked up

1:06:54.314 --> 1:06:57.448
over something that's probably
not even gonna happen.

1:06:57.491 --> 1:07:01.017
Listen, Daniella will not
be leaving this house.

1:07:01.060 --> 1:07:03.019
You have my word.

1:07:03.062 --> 1:07:06.718
And if you know anything about
me, you know my word is good.

1:07:06.761 --> 1:07:08.067
Now let's pray.

1:07:09.286 --> 1:07:11.853
[soft music fades]

1:07:13.116 --> 1:07:16.119
[insects buzzing]

1:07:18.643 --> 1:07:21.080
- Mind if I sit out
here with you for a bit?

1:07:21.124 --> 1:07:22.864
- Can't sleep?

1:07:22.908 --> 1:07:23.822
- Nope.

1:07:27.434 --> 1:07:29.610
- There you go.
- Thanks.

1:07:31.743 --> 1:07:34.702
[insects buzzing]

1:07:36.269 --> 1:07:39.577
- What do you wanna
do with your life?

1:07:40.795 --> 1:07:42.928
There must be something.

1:07:46.105 --> 1:07:49.239
- I want my mom
to wanna see me.

1:07:49.282 --> 1:07:51.937
- She doesn't wanna see you?

1:07:51.980 --> 1:07:53.417
- She told me the only reason

1:07:53.460 --> 1:07:56.333
she kept me around
was for the check.

1:07:56.376 --> 1:07:57.595
Said if it wasn't
for the check,

1:07:57.638 --> 1:08:00.424
she would've got
rid of me a long...

1:08:01.599 --> 1:08:05.733
long time ago.
[soft music]

1:08:05.777 --> 1:08:08.997
- So why do you wanna see her?

1:08:09.041 --> 1:08:10.738
- She's still my
mother, you know?

1:08:10.782 --> 1:08:13.567
I still want her
to be straight.

1:08:17.963 --> 1:08:20.226
Anyways, enough about
me. How about you?

1:08:20.270 --> 1:08:22.098
I mean, I see you
leaving the house

1:08:22.141 --> 1:08:24.448
every Sunday afternoon
around the same time.

1:08:24.491 --> 1:08:27.668
Not that I'm a creep or a
stalker or nothin' like that.

1:08:27.712 --> 1:08:31.933
It's just, I see you
leave and come back.

1:08:31.977 --> 1:08:36.242
- I go to AA meetings. I'm
a recovering alcoholic.

1:08:37.156 --> 1:08:38.853
I go on Thursdays, too.

1:08:38.897 --> 1:08:39.985
[Jaylen scoffs]

1:08:40.028 --> 1:08:41.552
- You, Ms. Grace?

1:08:42.553 --> 1:08:44.729
Wow, I don't know.

1:08:44.772 --> 1:08:49.647
You just to have it all
so together, you know?

1:08:49.690 --> 1:08:52.737
- [Grace] Everybody's
got struggles.

1:08:54.608 --> 1:08:58.656
- You know, I stopped
dreaming a long time ago.

1:08:58.699 --> 1:09:01.267
But since you've been here,
I mean, I'm dreaming again.

1:09:01.311 --> 1:09:04.488
And I don't know
what that means yet.

1:09:05.619 --> 1:09:08.318
But I hope it's something good.

1:09:09.841 --> 1:09:11.843
- Me, too.

1:09:11.886 --> 1:09:14.193
- Thanks. For the candy.

1:09:14.237 --> 1:09:17.544
You have a good
night, Ms. Grace.

1:09:17.588 --> 1:09:19.459
[soft music]

1:09:19.503 --> 1:09:23.115
- You too, Jalen.

1:09:23.159 --> 1:09:28.207
[soft music fades]
[insects buzzing]

1:09:38.652 --> 1:09:40.785
[sighs]

1:09:43.918 --> 1:09:48.053
- I am really tired
of you waking me up

1:09:48.096 --> 1:09:50.882
in the middle of
the night, God.

1:09:52.275 --> 1:09:54.233
I mean, because
you don't sleep,

1:09:54.277 --> 1:09:56.583
I shouldn't sleep either?

1:09:56.627 --> 1:09:58.716
[sighs]

1:09:58.759 --> 1:10:01.284
Couldn't we do this
in the morning,

1:10:01.327 --> 1:10:04.461
after I've had my coffee?

1:10:05.636 --> 1:10:08.508
[sighs]

1:10:13.209 --> 1:10:15.298
[sighs]

1:10:19.476 --> 1:10:21.521
"For if you forgive
men their trespasses,

1:10:21.565 --> 1:10:24.742
"your Heavenly Father
will also forgive you.

1:10:24.785 --> 1:10:26.961
"But if you not forgive
men their trespasses,

1:10:27.005 --> 1:10:29.225
"neither will your father
forgive your trespasses."

1:10:29.268 --> 1:10:32.489
Who have I not forgiven?

1:10:32.532 --> 1:10:35.666
I like the kids,
I like Michael.

1:10:37.885 --> 1:10:39.670
And I like Kimberly.
I..

1:10:41.498 --> 1:10:42.629
Oh no.

1:10:42.673 --> 1:10:44.109
No, no, no, no, no.

1:10:44.152 --> 1:10:45.937
No, no, no, no, no.

1:10:45.980 --> 1:10:47.852
No, not him!

1:10:47.895 --> 1:10:55.033
I mean, I was really
starting to feel good again.

1:10:57.688 --> 1:11:03.911
I was really starting to
get my foot hold again.

1:11:04.999 --> 1:11:08.916
[soft music]

1:11:13.617 --> 1:11:15.749
[sighs]

1:11:17.098 --> 1:11:19.579
[soft music]

1:11:24.018 --> 1:11:27.892
- He is such a
beautiful baby, Gracie.

1:11:27.935 --> 1:11:32.418
I'm sorry, but this is
what your father wanted.

1:11:32.462 --> 1:11:33.941
My brother can be
so mean sometimes-

1:11:33.985 --> 1:11:35.552
- But he was my baby.
- I know, Gracie.

1:11:35.595 --> 1:11:37.554
- Mine.
- I know.

1:11:41.297 --> 1:11:44.604
It was nice of that nurse to
let you have that picture.

1:11:44.648 --> 1:11:46.737
Gracie?

1:11:46.780 --> 1:11:51.263
Whatever you do, don't let
your daddy find it, okay?

1:11:53.787 --> 1:11:58.749
You keep it well hidden.
[car starts up]

1:12:00.011 --> 1:12:06.626
[Michael mumbling]

1:12:11.239 --> 1:12:14.199
- You don't just
give false promises

1:12:14.242 --> 1:12:16.549
when you can't come through.

1:12:16.593 --> 1:12:19.509
Givin' people hope.
Can't even deliver.

1:12:19.552 --> 1:12:22.599
- So they won't let her stay?

1:12:22.642 --> 1:12:24.122
- They don't care.

1:12:24.165 --> 1:12:27.778
- There's gotta be another way.

1:12:27.821 --> 1:12:30.563
- We've exhausted
every option, Grace.

1:12:30.607 --> 1:12:32.304
Other than going
out on our own,

1:12:32.348 --> 1:12:33.523
that's the only thing left.

1:12:33.566 --> 1:12:35.089
- Well then do that, Michael.

1:12:35.133 --> 1:12:36.656
Go off on your own.

1:12:36.700 --> 1:12:39.093
- With what, exactly?

1:12:39.137 --> 1:12:41.269
If we do that, we run the
risk of losing everything,

1:12:41.313 --> 1:12:43.533
maybe even the house.

1:12:43.576 --> 1:12:46.100
- They can't take your house.

1:12:47.972 --> 1:12:49.887
- We still got the mortgage.

1:12:49.930 --> 1:12:53.107
If we lose our funding, for
my salary, Kimberly's salary,

1:12:53.151 --> 1:12:55.936
and our medical insurance...

1:12:55.980 --> 1:12:57.808
- What about grants?

1:12:57.851 --> 1:13:00.332
I know that there are grants
for communities like this.

1:13:00.376 --> 1:13:02.639
I mean, the house is beautiful,

1:13:02.682 --> 1:13:04.684
but maybe you should...

1:13:07.034 --> 1:13:09.646
- You remember Sam's situation.

1:13:09.689 --> 1:13:12.083
That's why we stayed
under their umbrella.

1:13:12.126 --> 1:13:15.042
- So you're not gonna give up?

1:13:15.086 --> 1:13:17.393
- Not on all of 'em.

1:13:17.436 --> 1:13:19.351
- What does that mean?

1:13:21.092 --> 1:13:23.442
- It means I broke my word.

1:13:24.443 --> 1:13:27.185
[Grace sighs]

1:13:38.109 --> 1:13:40.024
[soft piano music]

1:13:40.067 --> 1:13:41.242
- Here.

1:13:41.286 --> 1:13:42.983
- What is that?

1:13:43.027 --> 1:13:43.810
- I wrote it.

1:13:43.854 --> 1:13:45.290
For you.

1:13:45.333 --> 1:13:49.076
- And you're giving
it to me because?

1:13:49.120 --> 1:13:51.383
- It's for you. [laughs]

1:13:51.427 --> 1:13:54.081
Thought that was implied.

1:13:54.125 --> 1:13:55.605
- You're not scared
I'm gonna slap

1:13:55.648 --> 1:13:58.521
you in the face like
your mom or whatever?

1:14:00.523 --> 1:14:02.916
- You know what? Forget it.

1:14:04.831 --> 1:14:07.443
Look, one of these
days, you're gonna need

1:14:07.486 --> 1:14:09.488
somebody in your corner,
and if it's not me,

1:14:09.532 --> 1:14:11.142
fine, that's whatever.

1:14:11.185 --> 1:14:14.145
But you're gonna need
a friend, a true one.

1:14:14.188 --> 1:14:15.929
- So you find out I'm
leaving and all of a sudden,

1:14:15.973 --> 1:14:18.279
you wanna be my friend?

1:14:18.323 --> 1:14:21.239
Feels a little convenient,
don't you think?

1:14:21.282 --> 1:14:24.416
- You just don't
get it, do you?

1:14:24.460 --> 1:14:25.373
I'm done.

1:14:27.288 --> 1:14:40.867
[melancholy music]

1:14:45.524 --> 1:14:47.744
- Langston, if you
just hear me out,

1:14:47.787 --> 1:14:50.311
you'll see that the
Devlin House is everything

1:14:50.355 --> 1:14:54.185
that we used to dream
about being a part of.

1:14:54.228 --> 1:14:55.665
- The projects
that we've chosen

1:14:55.708 --> 1:14:57.971
have large-scale,
global impact.

1:14:58.015 --> 1:15:00.104
That was your idea
from the beginning.

1:15:00.147 --> 1:15:01.975
You want us to just
set those aside

1:15:02.019 --> 1:15:04.238
and focus on a house
with a handful of kids

1:15:04.282 --> 1:15:05.631
from a dying community?

1:15:05.675 --> 1:15:07.067
- Just come.
- Grace.

1:15:07.111 --> 1:15:08.025
- Just come. Come
meet the kids.

1:15:08.068 --> 1:15:09.461
See the kids, listen.

1:15:09.505 --> 1:15:10.636
- This house is just
one of thousands

1:15:10.680 --> 1:15:12.551
of programs that need our help.

1:15:12.595 --> 1:15:15.293
We can't save them all.

1:15:15.336 --> 1:15:17.251
[Langston sighs]

1:15:17.295 --> 1:15:21.517
Look, I'm worried
about you burning out.

1:15:21.560 --> 1:15:24.215
That's the last thing you
need during a recovery.

1:15:24.258 --> 1:15:27.435
- Langston, I've
never felt so alive.

1:15:28.959 --> 1:15:30.830
Nice catching up.

1:15:30.874 --> 1:15:35.879
[soft music]

1:15:42.581 --> 1:15:45.671
- Can't we do like a bake
sale or a raffle or somethin'?

1:15:45.715 --> 1:15:49.153
Isn't that what people
do when they need money?

1:15:49.196 --> 1:15:51.329
- I vote bake sale.

1:15:51.372 --> 1:15:52.809
I could get with some edibles.

1:15:52.852 --> 1:15:54.158
- Okay, dude, those
kind of edibles

1:15:54.201 --> 1:15:56.769
will get you locked up again.

1:15:56.813 --> 1:15:58.379
- That's it.

1:15:58.423 --> 1:15:59.990
- Really?

1:16:00.033 --> 1:16:01.426
- Okay, Selina does
have a point, though.

1:16:01.469 --> 1:16:02.601
I can't be caught
with anything.

1:16:02.645 --> 1:16:04.908
- Uh-uh, no Q, no.

1:16:04.951 --> 1:16:08.781
I'm talking about a fundraiser.

1:16:08.825 --> 1:16:10.609
A concert.

1:16:10.653 --> 1:16:13.003
- Yeah, no disrespect, but
that's a terrible idea.

1:16:13.046 --> 1:16:15.745
- Yeah, Ms. Grace, and
you promised us no choir.

1:16:15.788 --> 1:16:17.616
- A showcase, then.

1:16:17.660 --> 1:16:19.705
You don't have to sing.

1:16:19.749 --> 1:16:22.360
Jalen, you'll write.

1:16:22.403 --> 1:16:24.884
It's time for you to
show this community

1:16:24.928 --> 1:16:27.017
the power of your words.

1:16:27.060 --> 1:16:29.759
And Tay, I've seen
your paintings.

1:16:29.802 --> 1:16:31.238
You are amazing.

1:16:31.282 --> 1:16:33.937
We can sell your artwork.

1:16:33.980 --> 1:16:35.852
And I'm sure that
there's at least someone

1:16:35.895 --> 1:16:37.331
here who can sing.

1:16:37.375 --> 1:16:39.420
- Okay wait, let me
get this straight.

1:16:39.464 --> 1:16:42.206
You want us to do all of
this for Daniella, right?

1:16:42.249 --> 1:16:43.511
- [Grace] Yes.

1:16:45.775 --> 1:16:48.038
- Think about it, you guys.

1:16:48.081 --> 1:16:49.605
Would she do that for us?

1:16:49.648 --> 1:16:50.649
- No.

1:16:50.693 --> 1:16:51.868
- No.
- Nope.

1:16:51.911 --> 1:16:54.740
- Look, you all
want to be safe.

1:16:54.784 --> 1:16:57.743
We can raise enough money
to go out on our own

1:16:57.787 --> 1:17:00.528
so that we're no longer
underneath this organization

1:17:00.572 --> 1:17:04.663
that doesn't care about you
the way that the Devlin's do.

1:17:04.707 --> 1:17:07.361
And, at the very
least, we can gain some

1:17:07.405 --> 1:17:09.929
support from the community.

1:17:09.973 --> 1:17:13.237
This thing that's
happening with Daniella,

1:17:13.280 --> 1:17:18.808
this is only a small part
of a big, big problem.

1:17:18.851 --> 1:17:21.506
Now, you wanna take
your power back?

1:17:21.549 --> 1:17:25.641
This is your chance
to stand up and fight.

1:17:27.338 --> 1:17:29.862
- [Jalen] I've got you.

1:17:29.906 --> 1:17:33.257
- We really gonna do
this, Mr. Michael?

1:17:33.300 --> 1:17:34.301
- For real.

1:17:37.000 --> 1:17:39.219
[chuckles]
- All right, everybody.

1:17:39.263 --> 1:17:41.134
The photographer's
gonna be here in an hour

1:17:41.178 --> 1:17:45.051
and they wanna do a story on
the house and the showcase.

1:17:45.095 --> 1:17:46.400
- [Jalen] That's right.

1:17:46.444 --> 1:17:47.924
- Are you kidding?
- Newspaper bro.

1:17:47.967 --> 1:17:49.316
We're gonna be famous,
my guy, famous.

1:17:49.360 --> 1:17:51.449
- We're gonna be famous.
[laughing]

1:17:51.492 --> 1:17:52.450
- [Jalen] You'll be famous-ish.

1:17:52.493 --> 1:17:53.364
I mean...

1:17:53.407 --> 1:17:54.800
- Whoa, bro, yo.

1:17:54.844 --> 1:17:55.932
You kidding me right now?

1:17:55.975 --> 1:17:57.716
- Hold up, Sam.

1:17:57.760 --> 1:17:59.805
It's all right, it's all right.

1:17:59.849 --> 1:18:01.589
- On the posters, like-
- He can't help it.

1:18:01.633 --> 1:18:03.156
You guys know he can't help it.

1:18:03.200 --> 1:18:05.202
- I'm sorry.
- It's okay, baby.

1:18:05.245 --> 1:18:07.987
It's all right. It's all right.

1:18:08.031 --> 1:18:10.903
How long has this
been going on?

1:18:10.947 --> 1:18:16.430
- It happens mostly when
I'm distressed or excited.

1:18:16.474 --> 1:18:20.086
I don't know. It's
just, I guess I'm weird.

1:18:20.130 --> 1:18:23.089
It does wonders for my clout.

1:18:23.133 --> 1:18:25.439
- There's something
special about you.

1:18:25.483 --> 1:18:27.572
- Right.
- Something rare,

1:18:27.615 --> 1:18:31.489
and people, you're
gonna change people.

1:18:31.532 --> 1:18:33.578
- Right.
- Yes.

1:18:33.621 --> 1:18:37.060
- Trailer trash with
meth head parents.

1:18:37.103 --> 1:18:39.889
- That's not who you are and
your future, your family,

1:18:39.932 --> 1:18:45.677
it doesn't define who you are
or where you're going, baby.

1:18:45.721 --> 1:18:46.896
Sam.
- Ms. Grace,

1:18:46.939 --> 1:18:49.289
I don't wanna make posters.

1:18:50.203 --> 1:18:52.249
- What?

1:18:52.292 --> 1:18:55.774
- I don't wanna make posters.
- Okay.

1:18:55.818 --> 1:18:58.734
So what would you
like to do, Sam?

1:19:00.126 --> 1:19:01.911
- I wanna play.

1:19:03.826 --> 1:19:07.917
[chattering]

1:19:22.018 --> 1:19:23.106
- [Tay] Ms. Grace,
what are you doing?

1:19:23.149 --> 1:19:26.762
You know he has-
- Shh.

1:19:39.687 --> 1:19:41.472
[soft piano music]

1:19:41.515 --> 1:19:44.431
Okay, so he knows how
to make a few chords.

1:19:44.475 --> 1:19:50.089
[soft piano music]

1:19:54.659 --> 1:19:59.838
♪ There's so many days that I
Feel that familiar ♪

1:20:00.752 --> 1:20:05.104
♪ Ache in my soul

1:20:05.148 --> 1:20:07.759
♪ Thrown away so carelessly

1:20:07.803 --> 1:20:09.630
♪ A forgotten memory

1:20:09.674 --> 1:20:15.027
♪ Guess I didn't
suit how you roll ♪

1:20:15.071 --> 1:20:20.554
♪ How could I ever be whole

1:20:20.598 --> 1:20:25.733
♪ You took me from my
fantasy of a family ♪

1:20:25.777 --> 1:20:30.913
♪ Abandoned me
along with my name ♪

1:20:32.131 --> 1:20:35.439
♪ Oh, no, finding my heart

1:20:35.482 --> 1:20:38.398
♪ In the darkness

1:20:38.442 --> 1:20:43.534
♪ Alone before I could fly

1:20:43.577 --> 1:20:48.408
♪ And searching for you,
oh I found the truth ♪

1:20:48.452 --> 1:20:53.718
♪ In the life painted
with the lies ♪

1:20:53.761 --> 1:20:56.764
♪ No, life is a tapestry

1:20:56.808 --> 1:21:03.380
♪ Beautifully woven
from discarded things ♪

1:21:03.423 --> 1:21:07.775
♪ Like me

1:21:08.951 --> 1:21:14.347
[soft piano music]

1:21:18.961 --> 1:21:21.485
- [Jalen] Are you kidding me?

1:21:21.528 --> 1:21:24.140
[laughing]

1:21:24.183 --> 1:21:28.274
- Oh my gosh. Okay,
so Sam can sing, too?

1:21:28.318 --> 1:21:30.842
No, I take that
back. Sam can sang.

1:21:30.886 --> 1:21:33.714
[laughing]

1:21:33.758 --> 1:21:38.241
- I heard what you
guys are doing.

1:21:38.284 --> 1:21:40.634
I don't get it, I wouldn't
do the same for any of you.

1:21:40.678 --> 1:21:42.201
[Jalen chuckles]

1:21:42.245 --> 1:21:44.334
- [All] We know.

1:21:44.377 --> 1:21:47.032
- Face it, Daniella,
we got you.

1:21:47.076 --> 1:21:49.774
That's what family does.
- Yeah.

1:21:51.036 --> 1:21:53.343
- Sam.

1:22:10.621 --> 1:22:13.232
- Thank you, Langston.

1:22:13.276 --> 1:22:16.714
Well, I really appreciate
you taking the time to call.

1:22:16.757 --> 1:22:18.542
- [Langston] Well they
must really need you there.

1:22:18.585 --> 1:22:20.761
- I need them.

1:22:20.805 --> 1:22:22.589
[phone beeps]

1:22:22.633 --> 1:22:24.417
Langston, listen I've gotta go.

1:22:24.461 --> 1:22:26.419
I've gotta another call. I
call you back later, okay?

1:22:26.463 --> 1:22:29.422
- Oh yeah, sure,
sure, sure. Sure.

1:22:32.164 --> 1:22:34.862
- Mom?

1:22:39.476 --> 1:22:42.609
- Um, where are you going?

1:22:42.653 --> 1:22:45.221
- Oh, I'm going to
visit my family.

1:22:45.264 --> 1:22:48.746
- Oh, for a minute I
thought you might be...

1:22:48.789 --> 1:22:50.878
That's besides the point.

1:22:50.922 --> 1:22:54.317
Yeah, that's great. [chuckles]

1:22:54.360 --> 1:22:57.102
Oh, um, you know,
my mom called.

1:22:57.146 --> 1:23:01.715
They told me she wanted to see
me, so, I'm gonna go do that.

1:23:01.759 --> 1:23:03.500
- I'm happy for you, Jay.

1:23:03.543 --> 1:23:04.675
And I know it's
something that you've

1:23:04.718 --> 1:23:06.503
been wanting for quite a while.

1:23:06.546 --> 1:23:08.374
- Yeah.
- I'm happy.

1:23:08.418 --> 1:23:09.506
- Well um...

1:23:13.118 --> 1:23:14.467
Be safe.

1:23:14.511 --> 1:23:15.947
- I will.

1:23:15.991 --> 1:23:18.036
You too, sweetheart.
- Yes, ma'am.

1:23:18.080 --> 1:23:20.473
See you soon?
- See you soon.

1:23:22.127 --> 1:23:24.651
- [Jalen] Have fun.

1:23:24.695 --> 1:23:28.046
[soft music]
[insects buzzing]

1:23:28.090 --> 1:23:32.746
- I wish you had
told me about Eric.

1:23:34.661 --> 1:23:38.926
- Mama, you've got enough
to deal with right now.

1:23:43.105 --> 1:23:44.932
- Here, I'ma give you
some more of this cake.

1:23:44.976 --> 1:23:46.499
- Oh mama.
- Come on, you can do it.

1:23:46.543 --> 1:23:48.327
- But mama.
[chuckling]

1:23:48.371 --> 1:23:51.287
It is so, ooh, so good.

1:23:51.330 --> 1:23:53.550
Oh, goodness gracious.

1:23:53.593 --> 1:23:57.554
You know, I can't even
remember the last time

1:23:57.597 --> 1:24:00.339
I got to enjoy
your cooking, mm.

1:24:01.123 --> 1:24:02.080
- Oh.

1:24:03.560 --> 1:24:06.693
It was a beautiful
Sunday morning.

1:24:06.737 --> 1:24:10.219
It was just a little
piece of spring in tHe air

1:24:10.262 --> 1:24:14.571
and I made apple sauce.

1:24:14.614 --> 1:24:17.182
I cut the apples up myself.

1:24:17.226 --> 1:24:19.750
And bacon.

1:24:19.793 --> 1:24:23.928
And scrambled eggs,
the way you like it.

1:24:25.277 --> 1:24:28.933
I made, uh, hash browns.

1:24:28.976 --> 1:24:32.676
And ooh, my famous gravy.

1:24:32.719 --> 1:24:36.419
Oh yeah, it was beautiful,
